      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks, these are really helpful. i feel like the \"slippery slope\" argument is the most powerful part of my post. given how much power the state has, isn't it basically a fact that any regulation inevitably leads to the kind of authoritarianism arendt warned about? it feels like there's no middle ground where regulation stays \"safe\" and doesn't eventually become censorship.",
